org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.spark.structure.io

Interface InputRDD

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InputFormatRDD, PersistedInputRDD

    public interface InputRDD
    An InputRDD is used to read data from the underlying graph system and yield the respective adjacency list. Note that InputFormatRDD is a type of InputRDD that simply uses the specified org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.InputFormat to generate the respective graphRDD.
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com)

                                  JavaSparkContext sparkContext)

        K - the key class of the memoryRDD

        Parameters:
        configuration - the configuration for the SparkGraphComputer
